<TITLE> Police arrest Bashundhara official in Gazipur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, May 14 (bdnews24.com)  Gazipur police arrested a senior Bashundhara company group official, early on Friday morning, on charges of trespassing on government property, cutting earth and threatening government officers. Masum Hossain, the detained man, is a senior administrative officer of Bashundhara's Mouchak City housing project. Gazipur's Kaliakair thana police chief Md Amir Hossain told bdnews24.com that Masum was arrested from the city's Maddhyapara area. On Thursday, Mohammed Mokhlesur Rahman, assistant land officer of Shafipur union, filed two cases against Bashundhara Group Ahmed Akbar Sobhan, popularly known as Shah Alam. The cases also charged another 40-50 unidentified people. The case statements said that on Apr 28, 40-50 Bashundhara Group workers, on orders of their chairman, entered the government property at Madhyaparha Mouja and dug away earth for land-filling their Bashundhara-Mouchak City Housing project. Officials of the union's land office were threatened with 'dire consequences' when they had tried to stop the Bashundhara men, the case stated. The next day, another 30-35 Bashundhara workers are alleged to have cut away earth from another government property in a similar manner. bdnews
